Nigerian actress and fashion designer, Toyin Lawani, has revealed that she will be canceling her proposed butt enlargement surgery due to the huge risk involved. This is coming after the death of a social media influencer, Christabel, who died of complications from a botched liposuction in a Nigerian hospital. According to Lawani in a post via her official Instagram page, people are dying from body enhancement surgeries which is scaring her. -Advertisement- She wrote, “Good morning y’all , I finally changed my mind, will manage the one the Lord gave me, to think I have paid, everything is just scaring me, the breast/lipo on stomach I have do is ok. People are dying. “Pls if you want to do any surgery go abroad, Every surgery has huge risk , but then again, Don’t go and carry yansh and give dentist o”